column5: Looking for fishing info for walleye in this area? Leaving on Aug. 13th.

The last reports I saw were that some of the guys were heading up to Yellow Girl to fish. Try this website, it also has a very good map that will show the reefs in the Whitefish Bay area. http://www.tomahawkresort.com/lakeofthewoods/

The walleye bite has been great, Sunset Channel has been producing and the reefs up north of that area (Whiteout,Shore Island) have also been producing.Today was catching fish in 30-35ft on minnows, leeches, and even plastic.Good luck.
